The paper deals with concurrent programming and resource management, which are topics commonly found in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses memory reclamation, which is a common problem in Operating Systems (cs.OS). The paper presents implementations for three common use cases, which suggests that it may fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the protection of read-destruct races, which is a topic related to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
